cafes.name: Eugene Springfield Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 537 W Centennial Blvd, Springfield, OR 97477, USA

text.text: I stopped in to look around and check the scene out.  The owner was welcoming, happening, and just ever so stern.  These are live, young animals here.  Care must be taken for the welfare of all involved here.  The kids love visiting and playing with the cats.  The adults love visiting the cats, and the cats, most of all, love the giving and receiving of attentions.  $15.00 an hour, I believe.  Fun, fun,fun.

We recently adopted a kitten from here. We already love her more than words can tell.
I like going even though I have cats at home. The kittens have a wide range of personalities. Some lounge and love to be pet the whole time you're there. Others enjoy a mix of cuddles and play time. The best are the few who are rowdy and will play with anything. I suggest going when they first open. The kitties are waking up and ready to PLAY!!!!!!
Lots of cute cats! Playful, and adoptable, and they seem very well taken care of and watched over. Not too expensive for an hour slot, and they even let you in for free on your birthday!

cafes.name: Flying Cat Coffee Co
cafes.address: 3041 SE Division St, Portland, OR 97202, USA

text.text: This is not a welcoming place. I came inside with friends, and the guy didn't serve us coffee in mugs. Immediately in to-go containers. I asked why. He said the business was going to close in 15 minutes. He could have been upfront and said that before we place the order. They also need a bigger sign outside showing their time it is going to be open and close. I do not recommend this place.
Good coffee and theme ðŸ™€. Food was also tasty. I like the zucchini bread too. Vegan options available.

Was looking for a Portland coffee shop that didnâ€™t have stark white walls with uncomfy chairsâ€”Flying Cat delivered a great experience in every way. Coffee was wonderful and the atmosphere was cozy for a Sunday afternoon.

cafes.name: The Country Cat
cafes.address: 7000 NE Airport Way, Portland, OR 97218, USA

text.text: Selene is one of the best bartenders I've ever encountered. Not just airport bartenders, but best bartenders period. Friendly and professional, she made there time enjoyable and had great suggestions for food and drinks. She's literally THE BEST!

Nice relaxing place to grab a bite before or after your flight. Wine selection was nice and the waitress/bartender selene (everything girl) was running around helping everyone with a smile and had so much patience with everyone for being slammed !

Lovely restaurant with a concise but varied menu of absolutely delicious food. The fried chicken sandwich was my favorite and I was pleased to find that it was a fried chicken thigh instead of the usual chicken breast. Moist and delicious and perfectly fried. My wife really enjoyed her chicken salad sandwich that had capers which was a unique salty twist that worked so well! Thanks for a great experience!
Cute little cafe .. we ordered a mocha with a gluten-free blueberry lemon coffee cake.. the owner was very sweet! We will be back ðŸ©µ
Such a wonderful place to visit. The gluten free baked goods are amazing! There's lots of fun drinks options as well. I go here whenever we are in the area running errands. Highly recommend!

The second you walk in the door you are greeted with a warm welcome and smile. The owner loves being a part of the community and it shows with the specialty menu items that pack great flavor and coffee drinks for all ages. Definitely a perfect drop in spot, good place to meet friends and hang out.

cafes.name: Playful Paws Cat CafÃ©
cafes.address: 1465 SW Knoll Ave Ste 102, Bend, OR 97702, USA

text.text: Itâ€™s like a shot of endorphins! Totally turned my mood around. The cats are happy and well cared for and best of all they are rescues seeking adoption ðŸ’—owner was friendly and happy to answer questions about the cats and knew about them all as individuals. Support this gem that helps cats find homes.

Wonderful staff and very friendly cats. The place is clean and welcoming. I also LOVE the mission of the business: matching adoptable cats with the right people and socializing them with cats/ people while waiting for the right match. My only reason for not giving 5 stars is the price to spend time with the cats feels high ($20 per person per 50 minutes). It was definitely a 'special occasion' outing for my daughter and me. We would go more often if it weren't so spendy.

I was super excited when I found out about this place. So I made plans for my five year old and I to meet up with a friend here.

I had looked over the website a bit already but was checking it out again the night before we were going to go. I saw a page for making a reservation and I thought Iâ€™d make one since we knew when we were going to meet up there. Only then did I see some small writing that said children under 8 are not permitted!

Iâ€™ve looked again and I only see two places on a very cluttered and busy website that say this important information that can really ruin your trip.

Itâ€™s fortunate I noticed this before my son and I drove out there and would have been turned away at the door. Can you imagine how he would have felt?

Itâ€™s unfortunate though that i had already TOLD him we were going to go pet and play with some cats the next morning. He was excited and would have loved it.

My five year old is super calm and gentle. More so than half the eight year olds Iâ€™ve seen. I wouldnâ€™t BRING him if he didnâ€™t know how to treat small animals. You canâ€™t judge a child by their age.

Disappointing a sweet little kid? Yeah thatâ€™s worth one star.

cafes.name: Coffee Cat Coffeehouse
cafes.address: 107 S College St, Newberg, OR 97132, USA

text.text: A cute coffee shop with lots of options. Me and my friends got a cinnamon roll, berry roll, smoothies, and bagels with cream cheese. All delicious! The smoothies were made with real fruit, not syrups. I got blueberry and it was delicious! Great atmosphere. Comfy couches in the back.

For a special treat me and my kids come here once a week. Their iced mocha is the BEST Iâ€™ve EVER had anywhere! I love the atmosphere and come here whenever I get the chance. They even remember that I like my drink extra sweet ðŸ˜‚
Stopped by to grab coffee and we ended up trying their bagels and cinnamon rolls. I loved the coffee and goodies! I definitely recommend stopping by. Very friendly baristas, too.

Seattle.name: NEKO Cat Cafe Seattle
Seattle.address: 519 E Pine St, Seattle, WA 98122, USA

text.text: This was such a great experience! we were in Seattle traveling for the week and missing our cats at home, so we decided to pop in for a visit! $25 for a 45 minute session with the cutest, sweetest, cats in Seattle! I definitely recommend coming here as the fee goes to a good cause, and you get a great experience out of it. Itâ€™s very clear that these cats are loved and well taken care of! I also recommend the Fez Mint Tea! It was delicious on that cold Seattle night. :)

I booked an appointment in advance to visit the Neko kitties. The staff was friendly and it was nice to have drinks and snacks available. The visit was 45 minutes long and time was shared with 8-10 cats and a few other people who had booked. I loved the cats even if many of them were ready for naps during our visit. Some of the cats are residents while others are available for adoption. Staff wipe down the space between visits. Well run cafe!  I'd love to go back if I'm ever back in Seattle!

Great experience. I had visited once before in passing for a beverage and a peek at the kitties, but I'm happy to have been able to book a visit with the kitties this time around. It was definitely worth it! Be sure to check out the sweet pickles collar bow ties if you're looking to spice up your own kitty's wardrobe.

cafes.name: Boring Bean formerly Cat's Moon Coffee

text.text: The employees are super nice and super workers.  They have fresh donuts from the neighboring town of Sandy, Joe's Donuts, brought in every day!  The garden is filled with cool-looking plants, some of which are for sale.  I enjoyed sipping my tea and walking on the little garden path.  I have nothing bad to say!
A wonderful discovery that was anything but Boring. Beautiful ambience, friendly staff, delicious coffee, pastries and so much more. Amazing space for plant parents
Only went in for coffee no food, that's why I did not rate the food. Also a great place to pick up some plants.

The whole idea behind a Catfe is amazing to me and Iâ€™m so glad that thereâ€™s a local business that executed the premise so well!! Admittedly if you get in and donâ€™t understand the process it could be a bit overwhelming. But pretty much you order your food, tell the cashier you want to spend time with the cats and itâ€™ll be a $10 charge per person (they got to feed the cats somehow) and theyâ€™ll have you sign a liability waver then boom! Youâ€™re in an airlock with cats for a whole hour! Service was great and extremely helpful throughout the whole process. Theyâ€™ve also got fantastic coffee so you donâ€™t have to worry about the quality dropping from having cats around.

A great place to sit down and have a cup of coffee and study, or chat. Happy to support the work they do.

I would love if there were more places to sit and observe the cats, but this doesn't stop me from coming.

We've already been a few times since finding this place a couple weeks ago. I already know a couple of the cats by name. The staff is amazing, the drinks are always delicious, so are the baked goods. Best membership I ever purchased! I always look forward to going, or making plans to go, with or without the kiddos. I mean it's coffee & kitty cats, how can you go wrong?!!  If you're thinking about going, just do it!!!
